{"body": "Unfortunately I never quite understood the intricate relationship details between `Relation` and `Association` - I kinda feel this should be better documented within Active Record, perhaps even mentioned in the Guides. It is indeed very confusing to see some calls dispatched here and others there, and even more confusing when you throw the occasional alias of some `Array`/`Enumerable` methods (but not others) into the mix.\r\n\r\nI remember a while back seeing a PR wanting to make `Association` subclass `Relation`, but not sure what happened to that.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/17736612", "created_at": "2013-05-10T18:27:57Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10539#issuecomment-17736612", "updated_at": "2013-05-10T18:27:57Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10539, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/egilburg", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/cc4f5494a8dcaaf577e678cb3901dab6?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F552d65b6e9616642fd0217dc7f8361bd.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg/received_events", "gravatar_id": "cc4f5494a8dcaaf577e678cb3901dab6", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "egilburg", "type": "User", "id": 242532, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/egilburg/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237dddcbd3543c151008b62"}, "id": 17736612, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10539"}
